- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is also likely as the paper discusses industrial solutions for utility computing, which may involve computational finance and science applications. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is relevant as the paper discusses the architecture of Utility Grids and how they can support utility computing. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) may be relevant as the paper may discuss software engineering challenges and solutions related to utility computing. 
- cs.Distributed Systems is also relevant as the paper discusses the use of Grid technologies for distributed resource allocation and management.
